text: Tucked away in the corner of a very tiny strip mall is this ABSOLUTELY FABULOUS place. I came in and it was empty,I was the only person here. The 2 women working behind the counter/kitchen couldn't have been more friendly and welcoming and suggestive when it came to me being indecisive about what I wanted to order. Food is flavorful,juicy,and just plain ole fashioned home cooked yumminess. I just wish this place had more visible signage alone the roadside.
This is the best place in Nevada for some good southern fried foods .You know the way your mother use to make it. Deliciously tasting and for a great price, food that feeds your soul.

Open 7 days a week
